@casesandberg Yeah, I see the problem.

Theoretically it could be:

``` js
ReactCSS.mixin.styles = function(){
  return this.css(this.conditionalClasses && this.conditionalClasses.call(this));
}
```

and when using this mixin:

``` js
var Item = React.createClass({
  mixins: [ReactCSS.mixin],
  // totaly optional now:
  conditionalClasses: function(){
    return {"hovered": this.state.hovered}
  }
```

And that way `conditionalClasses` will be an optional key only for those who want to declare conditional classes rules. All the rest won't have to declare `styles` at all.

But now it will probably be a breaking change for those who are already using it.

